  "text": "To clarify the other potential mechanism of the effect of PSR on PHLF, we found PSR to be a predictor (P<0.001, AUC 0.776) for liver cirrhosis which was the predominant risk factor for PHLF. A low PSR means a relatively low platelet count and a high value of SS, low platelet count and increased SS are the indirect indicators for liver cirrhosis and portal hypertension. An overperfusion from portal vein to a cirrhotic liver might lead to hepatic sinusoidal endothelium injury, delayed liver function recovery and PHLF [CITATION_1] .",
